item.title: Mind games (ep) Łevi
item.dc:creator: lowey
item.description:
I’m surprised you’ve not had any comments on this. It’s not really my cup of tea in terms of musical style, but the production values are high and there’s plenty of creativity in there. I felt like the piano got a little repetitive across a couple of the tracks, but other than that I’ve no real criticisms to make. I liked “Introduction” the best, it was probably the closest to my preferred style of music, and the drop about two thirds of the way through that track was awesome.
